>
  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6 italic text-gray-300">Andy and Gus play through <em>Halo: CE Anniversary</em> on Legendary difficulty in co-op via MCC. The playthrough is marked by recurring MCC co-op connectivity issues that caused multi-week gaps between recording sessions. Both hosts generally enjoy the Anniversary graphics, though they note the second half of the campaign suffers from repetitive level design — a product of its era.</p>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">General Observations</h2>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Difficulty:</strong> Legendary co-op throughout</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Graphics:</strong> Playing on Anniversary (remastered) graphics. The Halo rings and character models look especially good, though the environments look less impressive.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Weapons:</strong> The Magnum ("Vista Pistol") is widely acknowledged as broken/overpowered and is the most sought-after weapon throughout the run.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Assault Rifle:</strong> Praised for its high ammo count (~100 rounds), satisfying sound, and stopping power — considered one of the best ARs in the franchise.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">MCC Co-op:</strong> Persistent launch failures plagued the playthrough. The hosts note MCC co-op campaign has long-standing netcode issues that 343 has acknowledged but never fully resolved.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">The Pillar of Autumn</h2>

  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">The opening mission introduces the Anniversary visual toggle — old vs. new graphics can be swapped in real time. A <strong class="text-cyan-400">Halo 4 easter egg</strong> is visible early on: a dark planetoid called "Planetoid Rising" with a troll wall face.</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Spawning without a weapon at the start is noted as an annoyance on Legendary</li>
    <li>Overshields are available early in the level — one per player</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Bob</strong> (the hidden Elite from Reach) does <strong class="text-cyan-400">not</strong> appear in Halo CE</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Halo (The Ring)</h2>

  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">A large outdoor mission with Banshees, Warthogs, and a skull hunt. The hosts are going for a <strong class="text-cyan-400">no-vehicles achievement</strong>, making this mission significantly harder.</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Three Banshees need to be destroyed for an achievement — players need to kill them before elites can board</li>
    <li>Covenant drop ships actually <strong class="text-cyan-400">land</strong> in this game (Phantoms/Spirits set down), unlike in Reach where they hover</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Truth and Reconciliation</h2>

  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">A nighttime infiltration mission aboard a Covenant cruiser. Requires the <strong class="text-cyan-400">sniper rifle</strong> to take out the turret gunner silently at the start to unlock an achievement.</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Stealth opening:</strong> Kill the first group silently (crouching, sniper only) to get the achievement</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Halo 4 easter egg:</strong> A terminal reads "Linda — Cryo Chamber Status: Unavailable," referencing a Blue Team Spartan who appears in Halo 5</li>
    <li>Active camo is available on this mission; useful for getting close and meleeing enemies</li>
    <li>The turret can be hijacked — jumping into it triggers a chaotic sequence</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Foreign skull</strong> found behind the Hunters near the end of the level</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">The Silent Cartographer</h2>

  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">A beach/island mission. Notable for being one of the more enjoyable levels in the campaign.</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Jackal shields are noticeably harder to deal with in CE compared to later games — they hold shields more consistently</li>
    <li>The level has a distinct interior section with Hunters</li>
    <li>The hosts note the island/beach setting as one of the stronger level designs in the game</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Assault on the Control Room</h2>

  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">A long outdoor/indoor mission involving Wraiths, Banshees, Scorpion tanks, and a multi-story Forerunner structure.</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Scorpion tank</strong> is available but unwieldy — poor controls, limited field of view, screen shake</li>
    <li>Vehicles in Halo CE are <strong class="text-cyan-400">indestructible</strong> (unlike later games)</li>
    <li>The Ghost has no boost in this game</li>
    <li>The Forerunner structure interior is noted as a <strong class="text-cyan-400">visual match</strong> to the same location revisited in Halo 3</li>
    <li>This mission takes roughly 1+ hour to complete on Legendary</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">343 Guilty Spark</h2>

  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">Transition mission introducing the Flood. Short but atmospheric.</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>The Flood appear for the first time — "popcorn flood" (exploding infection forms) are the most notable threat</li>
    <li>Described as a great concept — parasitic rather than typical zombie trope</li>
    <li>One stray popcorn flood can block co-op respawns, causing frustration</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">The Library</h2>

  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">The most criticised mission in the campaign — long, repetitive, and fought entirely against the Flood across identical-looking rooms.</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Four floors</strong> of Forerunner structure, all visually near-identical</li>
    <li>Shotgun and assault rifle are the most effective weapons against the Flood</li>
    <li>Rocket-wielding Flood appear in the upper floors</li>
    <li>Hosts note this mission would be "ripped apart" by modern critics for its design</li>
    <li>The Sentinels (Forerunner drones) become active near the end; they are initially friendly</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Two Betrayals</h2>

  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">A revisit/reversal of Assault on the Control Room — same geometry, played in reverse.</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Three pulse generators must be destroyed; each requires a grenade thrown into a specific opening</li>
    <li>The rocket launcher can physically push/launch the grenade into the slot if used carefully</li>
    <li>Banshees are required to reach the third generator (it's elevated)</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Keyes</h2>

  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">Boarding the <em>Truth and Reconciliation</em> a second time, now overrun by Flood.</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>The level involves locating Captain Keyes in the brig — wrong doors are common</li>
    <li>Shotgun remains the best weapon against Flood</li>
    <li>The level's sewer/coolant environment is considered one of the better visual designs of the campaign</li>
    <li>Hunters appear unexpectedly on the ground floor</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">The Maw</h2>

  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">The escape mission — drive a Warthog through the exploding <em>Pillar of Autumn</em>.</p>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>The driving physics are notably poor — Warthog flips frequently on ramps</li>
    <li>One player riding the gun while the other drives is the most viable co-op approach</li>
    <li>The mission ends with the Chief escaping on a Longsword fighter as Halo detonates</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Final Thoughts</h2>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Halo CE Legendary</strong> is considered manageable, with the Flood-heavy back half being the hardest stretch</li>
    <li>The game "shows its age" in its second half but the core mechanics (gunplay, enemy archetypes) remain excellent</li>
    <li>Both hosts agree Halo 2 is a significant step up in campaign design</li>
    <li>MCC connectivity issues caused multiple multi-week gaps between recording sessions</li>
  </ul>
</BlogPostLayout>
